title: Policy6195(s2)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Only students in grades 9-12 are eligible to receive credit toward high school graduation by taking online courses. Students who have been pre-approved shall receive such credit upon completing the online course and obtaining a passing grade.

The Board of Education may, in its discretion, cover the cost for online courses that are not offered as in-class or online courses at RHAM. The Board of Education may also cover the cost of Virtual High School courses offered through the district's subscription with Virtual High School.
